    {
      "type": "range",
      "id": "section_spacing_mobile",
      "label": "Section spacing mobile",
      "min": 36,
      "max": 96,
      "step": 4,
      "default": 56
    },
    {
      "type": "range",
      "id": "section_spacing_desktop",
      "label": "Section spacing desktop",
      "min": 48,
      "max": 128,
      "step": 4,
      "default": 80
    },
    {
      "type": "header",
      "content": "Hero"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "hero_eyebrow",
      "label": "Eyebrow",
      "default": "Sustainability at Kaahu"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "hero_heading",
      "label": "Heading",
      "default": "What you carry should reflect what you value."
    },
    {
      "type": "textarea",
      "id": "hero_text",
      "label": "Intro text",
      "default": "So we account for it at every stage. Here is what that means, in plain terms, including the parts we have not finished yet."
    },
    {
      "type": "image_picker",
      "id": "hero_image",
      "label": "Hero image"
    },
    {
      "type": "richtext",
      "id": "intro_text",
      "label": "Opening copy",
      "default": "<p>Kaahu is shaped by the Hawaiian principle of <em>M&#257;lama</em> &mdash; to care for one&rsquo;s people, and for the land, air, and water that hold them. That care decides what we make, and how.</p><p>We choose natural fibers, low-impact methods, and partners who meet real standards. And we would rather move slowly than overstate.</p>"
    },
    {
      "type": "header",
      "content": "Materials"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "materials_eyebrow",
      "label": "Eyebrow",
      "default": "Materials"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "materials_heading",
      "label": "Heading",
